        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 30 at 4:22PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 422 PM EDT, National Weather Service doppler radar indicated a
line of strong thunderstorms along a line extending from Empire
to Lamar, and moving southeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...40 to 50 mph wind, pea sized hail, frequent cloud to
ground lightning and increased chance of a brief tornado.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...While winds should result in minor damage to tree limbs
and blowing around of light, unsecured objects, the
leading edge of this line of storms has also exhibited
areas of localized rotation. A brief tornado could
quickly form.

Locations impacted include...
Cordele, Eastman, Hawkinsville, Vienna, Abbeville, Rochelle, Arabi,
Pineview, Pinehurst, Rhine, Chauncey, Pitts, De Soto, Cobb, Union,
Lamar, Dubois, Richwood, Empire, and Plainfield.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for
central and west central Georgia.</instruction>
